5b6dc089-3af1-4600-a5aa-5ba6805afee6|{"server_conversation_token":"47dda3ee-c688-407a-b74b-f4854aef906d","todo_lists":[{"completed_items":[],"pending_items":[{"id":"94b2a33c-8ae2-43b0-b2ec-0ce23c51a49c","title":"Diagnose Current Smart Workspace Configuration","description":"Investigate why the smart workspace setup didn't work as expected:\n\n- Check if Ollama service is installed and running: `systemctl status ollama` or `ps aux | grep ollama`\n- Verify hypr-workspace-organizer script exists and is executable: `ls -la ~/.config/hypr/scripts/hypr-workspace-organizer`\n- Check environment variables in `~/.config/hypr/envs.conf` for AI settings (HYPR_ORGANIZER_USE_AI, OLLAMA_MODEL)\n- Review Hyprland keybindings in `~/.config/hypr/keybindings.conf` for SUPER+A and workspace organization shortcuts\n- Check logs for errors: `journalctl --user -u ollama -n 50` and `~/.local/share/hyprland/*.log`\n- Test if Ollama models are installed: `ollama list`"},{"id":"fb5f1dda-eeaa-4051-acac-110c9baf473c","title":"Search GitHub for Omarchy AI Integrations","description":"Research official and community repositories for AI features:\n\n- Search for \"omarchy ai\" on GitHub to find related projects\n- Look for the main Omarchy repository and check for AI-related branches or features\n- Search for \"hyprland ai workspace\" and \"hyprland ollama\" for community implementations\n- Identify repositories like omarchy-ai, hyprland-smart-workspace, or similar projects\n- Document repository URLs, stars, last update date, and key features\n- Check if any repos require GitHub authentication to access"},{"id":"8a616fcc-a830-4f0f-a799-c36d64f4d715","title":"Setup GitHub CLI Authentication","description":"Enable access to private repositories if needed:\n\n- Install GitHub CLI if not present: `sudo pacman -S github-cli`\n- Initiate authentication: `gh auth login`\n- Follow the browser-based authentication flow\n- Provide the authentication URL to the user for completion\n- Verify authentication: `gh auth status`\n- Test access to private repos: `gh repo list --limit 5`"},{"id":"583d89b5-825c-4384-b885-01dfad4dd2d6","title":"Clone and Analyze omarchy-ai Repository","description":"Deep dive into the omarchy-ai project structure and features:\n\n- Clone the repository: `git clone https://github.com/mitkox/omarchy-ai`\n- Examine README.md for features, requirements, and installation instructions\n- Review directory structure and identify key components\n- Check for AI model integration methods (Ollama, local inference, APIs)\n- Document automation scripts and their purposes\n- Identify Jupyter notebook integrations and AI development tools\n- List all dependencies and system requirements"},{"id":"052ba025-ce4d-43f4-95aa-d074195ec95d","title":"Enable and Test AI-Powered Smart Workspaces","description":"Configure the existing Omarchy installation to use AI features:\n\n- Start Ollama service: `systemctl --user enable --now ollama` or start manually\n- Install an appropriate model: `ollama pull llama2` or `ollama pull mistral`\n- Add environment variables to `~/.config/hypr/envs.conf`:\n  ```\n  env = HYPR_ORGANIZER_USE_AI,true\n  env = OLLAMA_MODEL,llama2\n  env = OLLAMA_HOST,http://localhost:11434\n  ```\n- Reload Hyprland configuration: `hyprctl reload`\n- Test manual workspace organization: Press SUPER+A\n- Open various applications and test AI categorization\n- Test interactive workspace switcher: Press SUPER+CTRL+W\n- Monitor logs for AI inference activity"},{"id":"2f1673fd-5710-47e5-9597-02e9c49d2cc4","title":"Compare Integration Options and Document Benefits","description":"Create a comprehensive comparison of AI integration approaches:\n\n**Current Setup Analysis:**\n- Built-in hypr-workspace-organizer capabilities\n- Ollama integration status\n- Rule-based vs AI-based categorization\n\n**omarchy-ai Benefits:**\n- Full AI development environment\n- Jupyter notebook integration for prototyping\n- Advanced model management\n- Custom automation scripts\n- Community-contributed AI workflows\n\n**Other Community Solutions:**\n- Alternative smart workspace implementations\n- Different AI model backends\n- Integration with other tools (rofi-ai, etc.)\n\nCreate a feature matrix comparing approaches with benefits listed for each."},{"id":"ae0f3c7a-9ead-456c-91dc-86606d3bd2ac","title":"Create Installation and Configuration Guides","description":"Develop step-by-step guides for different integration levels:\n\n**Level 1: Enable Existing AI Features**\n- Prerequisites (Ollama, models)\n- Configuration steps\n- Testing and validation\n- Troubleshooting common issues\n\n**Level 2: Install omarchy-ai Suite**\n- System requirements\n- Installation commands\n- Configuration integration with existing Omarchy\n- Additional features setup (Jupyter, model management)\n- Benefits over basic setup\n\n**Level 3: Custom Integrations**\n- How to add custom AI automations\n- Creating workspace rules\n- Integrating additional AI tools\n- Advanced configurations\n\nInclude estimated time, disk space, and complexity for each level."},{"id":"bf582b5a-2300-427d-a0d1-d6b3ad0c3e6c","title":"Test and Validate All AI Features","description":"Comprehensive testing of implemented AI integrations:\n\n- Test AI window categorization with various applications (browsers, terminals, IDEs, media players)\n- Verify workspace auto-organization triggers correctly\n- Test manual organization command (SUPER+A)\n- Validate workspace switcher functionality\n- Check performance impact of AI inference\n- Test fallback behavior when Ollama is unavailable\n- Document response times and accuracy\n- Create test scenarios for edge cases\n- Generate performance metrics report"},{"id":"5f03741e-a3a7-4e06-89ca-7c6436d61397","title":"Create Final Report with Recommendations","description":"Compile findings into actionable recommendations:\n\n**Current State Assessment:**\n- What's working and what's not\n- Root causes of initial issues\n- Quick fixes applied\n\n**Available Options:**\n- Comparison of all discovered AI integrations\n- Pros and cons of each approach\n- Resource requirements\n\n**Recommended Path:**\n- Best option for user's needs\n- Installation priority and sequence\n- Expected improvements\n\n**Next Steps:**\n- Immediate actions to take\n- Optional enhancements\n- Future possibilities\n\nInclude links to all repositories, documentation, and configuration files."}]}],"conversation_usage_metadata":{"was_summarized":false,"context_window_usage":0.547245,"credits_spent":91.68064,"credits_spent_for_last_block":86.296074,"token_usage":[{"model_id":"claude 4.5 sonnet (thinking)","total_tokens":887094,"byok_tokens":0},{"model_id":"gpt-5 (high reasoning)","total_tokens":26691,"byok_tokens":0}],"tool_usage_metadata":{"run_command_stats":{"count":36,"commands_executed":36},"read_files_stats":{"count":6},"search_codebase_stats":{"count":0},"grep_stats":{"count":1},"file_glob_stats":{"count":3},"apply_file_diff_stats":{"count":0,"lines_added":0,"lines_removed":0,"files_changed":0},"write_to_long_running_shell_command_stats":{"count":0},"read_mcp_resource_stats":{"count":0},"call_mcp_tool_stats":{"count":0},"suggest_plan_stats":{"count":1},"suggest_create_plan_stats":{"count":1},"read_shell_command_output_stats":{"count":0}}}}|2025-11-11 19:01:56
33d7cac8-86cb-4971-a356-58cd34420f2a|{"server_conversation_token":"9fb91ed1-2271-4b83-874b-3d334f90cf97","todo_lists":[{"completed_items":[{"id":"c33e4bf3-5ede-4a35-b293-fb924bb3d3da","title":"Backup existing configuration files","description":"Create backups of the configuration files we'll be modifying to ensure we can roll back if needed:\n\n```bash\ncp ~/.config/waybar/config.jsonc ~/.config/waybar/config.jsonc.backup\ncp ~/.config/hypr/bindings.conf ~/.config/hypr/bindings.conf.backup\n```"},{"id":"3f6a783e-ec15-4f4e-86a2-1ff7d86415b8","title":"Extend Waybar configuration to support 10 workspaces","description":"Update `/home/rob/.config/waybar/config.jsonc` to add workspaces 6-10:\n\n- Add icons for workspaces 6-10 in the `format-icons` section\n- Add workspaces 6-10 to `persistent-workspaces` to ensure they're always visible\n- Use appropriate icons (6: \"Ōæź\", 7: \"Ōæ”\", 8: \"Ōæ¦\", 9: \"Ōæ©\", 10: \"Ōæ®\" or similar)\n\nThis ensures the workspace bar displays all 10 workspaces."},{"id":"41fab529-ebbc-4636-958b-d0df2babc948","title":"Add Hyprland keybindings for workspace 10","description":"Update `/home/rob/.config/hypr/bindings.conf` to add:\n\n- `bind = SUPER, 0, workspace, 10` (keycode 19 for the 0 key)\n- `bind = SUPER SHIFT, 0, movetoworkspace, 10`\n\nThis allows switching to workspace 10 with SUPER+0 and moving windows there with SUPER+SHIFT+0."},{"id":"bbb65e65-923b-4a01-a914-e24bbcca73a1","title":"Reload Waybar to apply workspace changes","description":"Execute the following command to reload Waybar without restarting:\n\n```bash\npkill -SIGUSR2 waybar\n```\n\nThis applies the new workspace configuration immediately."},{"id":"851475ae-580a-423c-9ce1-7924f7a7cc8a","title":"Implement persistent workspace names/labels","description":"Create a configuration file `~/.config/hypr/workspace-names.json` to define custom workspace names:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"1\": \"Dev\",\n  \"2\": \"Web\",\n  \"3\": \"Chat\",\n  \"4\": \"Media\",\n  \"5\": \"Work\",\n  \"6\": \"Misc\",\n  \"7\": \"Games\",\n  \"8\": \"Files\",\n  \"9\": \"System\",\n  \"10\": \"Temp\"\n}\n```\n\nUpdate the workspace switcher and overview scripts to read and display these labels instead of just numbers."},{"id":"33125829-4c2d-49e8-9bff-1bd26ea045b4","title":"Create workspace switcher script with fuzzy finding","description":"Create `~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-switcher` that provides an interactive workspace switcher using rofi/wofi:\n\nThe script should:\n- Query all workspaces using `hyprctl workspaces -j`\n- Display workspace numbers with window counts\n- Show active workspace indicator (Ōśģ or highlight)\n- Display the last window title for each workspace\n- Use rofi/wofi with fuzzy finding for quick navigation\n- Switch to the selected workspace\n\nMake the script executable: `chmod +x ~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-switcher`"},{"id":"fae6f22b-4fd2-4dde-9125-2c7e7b577b49","title":"Create smart navigation script for non-empty workspaces","description":"Create `~/.local/bin/hypr-next-nonempty` that intelligently navigates to the next/previous workspace that has windows:\n\nThe script should:\n- Accept a parameter for direction (next/previous)\n- Query workspaces using `hyprctl workspaces -j`\n- Find the next/previous non-empty workspace in a circular manner\n- Switch to that workspace using `hyprctl dispatch workspace`\n\nMake the script executable: `chmod +x ~/.local/bin/hypr-next-nonempty`"},{"id":"b21f4d6d-0be8-47a4-b338-dc6385dbf9c1","title":"Create workspace rules configuration file","description":"Create `~/.config/hypr/workspace-rules.json` with a JSON structure defining automatic organization rules:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"rules\": [\n    {\"pattern\": \"firefox|chromium|brave\", \"type\": \"class\", \"workspace\": 2, \"category\": \"browsers\"},\n    {\"pattern\": \"kitty|alacritty|wezterm|foot\", \"type\": \"class\", \"workspace\": 1, \"category\": \"terminals\"},\n    {\"pattern\": \"code|neovim|vscodium\", \"type\": \"class\", \"workspace\": 1, \"category\": \"development\"},\n    {\"pattern\": \"signal|whatsapp|telegram|discord\", \"type\": \"class\", \"workspace\": 3, \"category\": \"communication\"},\n    {\"pattern\": \"spotify|vlc|mpv\", \"type\": \"class\", \"workspace\": 4, \"category\": \"media\"},\n    {\"pattern\": \"obsidian|thunderbird|evolution\", \"type\": \"class\", \"workspace\": 5, \"category\": \"productivity\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThis file will be used by the auto-organization system."},{"id":"6ed80ef6-9536-4094-85de-e981611bafbb","title":"Create AI-powered workspace organizer script","description":"Create `~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-organizer` in Python that:\n\n- Reads rules from `~/.config/hypr/workspace-rules.json`\n- Fetches all windows using `hyprctl clients -j`\n- Analyzes window class, title, and type\n- Applies rule-based categorization with regex matching\n- Optionally integrates with a local LLM API (Ollama) or OpenAI API for intelligent categorization of unmatched windows\n- Moves windows to appropriate workspaces using `hyprctl dispatch movetoworkspacesilent`\n- Maintains a learning file at `~/.config/hypr/workspace-learning.json` to track user corrections and preferences\n- Provides a notification summary of moves using notify-send\n\nDependencies to install: `python-requests` for API calls if using AI enhancement.\n\nMake the script executable: `chmod +x ~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-organizer`"},{"id":"fe63f045-1545-4899-91b2-5e2896261d3f","title":"Add navigation keybindings to Hyprland","description":"Update `/home/rob/.config/hypr/bindings.conf` to add:\n\n- `bind = SUPER, W, exec, ~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-switcher` (workspace switcher)\n- `bind = SUPER, N, exec, ~/.local/bin/hypr-next-nonempty next` (next non-empty workspace)\n- `bind = SUPER SHIFT, N, exec, ~/.local/bin/hypr-next-nonempty prev` (previous non-empty workspace)"},{"id":"52b9d1c9-c70e-47af-9625-0fbf24bf2187","title":"Add keybinding for manual workspace auto-organization","description":"Update `/home/rob/.config/hypr/bindings.conf` to add:\n\n- `bind = SUPER, A, exec, ~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-organizer`\n\nThis allows triggering the AI-powered organization on-demand with SUPER+A."},{"id":"e53b4934-f1c8-40cc-95c5-aa21da95da50","title":"Add Hyprland windowrulev2 directives for automatic workspace assignment","description":"Add windowrulev2 rules to `/home/rob/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf` (or a separate rules file) to automatically assign new windows to workspaces:\n\n```\nwindowrulev2 = workspace 2, class:^(firefox|chromium|brave)$\nwindowrulev2 = workspace 1, class:^(kitty|alacritty|foot|Code)$\nwindowrulev2 = workspace 3, class:^(Signal|whatsapp|telegram|discord)$\nwindowrulev2 = workspace 4, class:^(Spotify|vlc|mpv)$\nwindowrulev2 = workspace 5, class:^(obsidian|thunderbird)$\n```\n\nThis ensures windows open in the correct workspace automatically."},{"id":"439053f7-407d-4b1c-ad2e-f284cd860857","title":"Create comprehensive documentation","description":"Create `~/.config/hypr/WORKSPACE_GUIDE.md` documenting:\n\n- Overview of the 10-workspace system\n- Keybindings reference (all workspace-related shortcuts)\n- Workspace naming conventions and default assignments\n- How to use the AI auto-organization feature\n- How to customize workspace rules in `workspace-rules.json`\n- How the learning system works in `workspace-learning.json`\n- Troubleshooting tips\n- Examples of common workflows\n\nInclude clear markdown formatting with sections, code blocks, and tables."},{"id":"504c5386-4e1a-4983-83a8-b8da44d48dd6","title":"Create workspace overview script","description":"Create `~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-overview` that provides a visual overview of all workspaces:\n\nThe script should:\n- Query all workspaces and their windows using `hyprctl workspaces -j` and `hyprctl clients -j`\n- Generate a formatted display showing each workspace with:\n  - Workspace number and name/label\n  - List of windows with titles\n  - Window counts\n  - Active workspace indicator\n- Display using rofi/wofi or generate HTML for a browser-based overview\n- Allow clicking/selecting to switch to a workspace\n\nMake the script executable: `chmod +x ~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-overview`"},{"id":"52bbd10e-0198-4516-bbd8-25152d91e2f5","title":"Install hyprsome for enhanced workspace management","description":"Install hyprsome from the AUR to enable GNOME-like workspace behavior with automatic workspace creation/destruction:\n\n```bash\nyay -S hyprsome-git\n```\n\nThen add hyprsome to your Hyprland startup in `~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf` or the appropriate exec-once section."},{"id":"8d7efa80-f882-4d16-a59c-a1a43f63dc16","title":"Reload Hyprland configuration to apply all changes","description":"Execute the following command to reload the Hyprland configuration:\n\n```bash\nhyprctl reload\n```\n\nAlternatively, restart Hyprland completely if needed. This applies all the new bindings, window rules, and configuration changes."}],"pending_items":[]}],"conversation_usage_metadata":{"was_summarized":false,"context_window_usage":0.609925,"credits_spent":118.798,"credits_spent_for_last_block":118.798,"token_usage":[{"model_id":"claude 4.1 opus","total_tokens":482663,"byok_tokens":0}],"tool_usage_metadata":{"run_command_stats":{"count":2,"commands_executed":1},"read_files_stats":{"count":1},"search_codebase_stats":{"count":0},"grep_stats":{"count":0},"file_glob_stats":{"count":0},"apply_file_diff_stats":{"count":1,"lines_added":12,"lines_removed":3,"files_changed":1},"write_to_long_running_shell_command_stats":{"count":0},"read_mcp_resource_stats":{"count":0},"call_mcp_tool_stats":{"count":0},"suggest_plan_stats":{"count":0},"suggest_create_plan_stats":{"count":0},"read_shell_command_output_stats":{"count":0}}}}|2025-11-11 03:26:08
