\"category\": \"development\"},\n    {\"pattern\": \"signal|whatsapp|telegram|discord\", \"type\": \"class\", \"workspace\": 3, \"category\": \"communication\"},\n    {\"pattern\": \"spotify|vlc|mpv\", \"type\": \"class\", \"workspace\": 4, \"category\": \"media\"},\n    {\"pattern\": \"obsidian|thunderbird|evolution\", \"type\": \"class\", \"workspace\": 5, \"category\": \"productivity\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThis file will be used by the auto-organization system."},{"id":"6ed80ef6-9536-4094-85de-e981611bafbb","title":"Create AI-powered workspace organizer script","description":"Create `~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-organizer` in Python that:\n\n- Reads rules from `~/.config/hypr/workspace-rules.json`\n- Fetches all windows using `hyprctl clients -j`\n- Analyzes window class, title, and type\n- Applies rule-based categorization with regex matching\n- Optionally integrates with a local LLM API (Ollama) or OpenAI API for intelligent categorization of unmatched windows\n- Moves windows to appropriate workspaces using `hyprctl dispatch movetoworkspacesilent`\n- Maintains a learning file at `~/.config/hypr/workspace-learning.json` to track user corrections and preferences\n- Provides a notification summary of moves using notify-send\n\nDependencies to install: `python-requests` for API calls if using AI enhancement.\n\nMake the script executable: `chmod +x ~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-organizer`"},{"id":"fe63f045-1545-4899-91b2-5e2896261d3f","title":"Add navigation keybindings to Hyprland","description":"Update `/home/rob/.config/hypr/bindings.conf` to add:\n\n- `bind = SUPER, W, exec, ~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-switcher` (workspace switcher)\n- `bind = SUPER, N, exec, ~/.local/bin/hypr-next-nonempty next` (next non-empty workspace)\n- `bind = SUPER SHIFT, N, exec, ~/.local/bin/hypr-next-nonempty prev` (previous non-empty workspace)"},{"id":"52b9d1c9-c70e-47af-9625-0fbf24bf2187","title":"Add keybinding for manual workspace auto-organization","description":"Update `/home/rob/.config/hypr/bindings.conf` to add:\n\n- `bind = SUPER, A, exec, ~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-organizer`\n\nThis allows triggering the AI-powered organization on-demand with SUPER+A."},{"id":"e53b4934-f1c8-40cc-95c5-aa21da95da50","title":"Add Hyprland windowrulev2 directives for automatic workspace assignment","description":"Add windowrulev2 rules to `/home/rob/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf` (or a separate rules file) to automatically assign new windows to workspaces:\n\n```\nwindowrulev2 = workspace 2, class:^(firefox|chromium|brave)$\nwindowrulev2 = workspace 1, class:^(kitty|alacritty|foot|Code)$\nwindowrulev2 = workspace 3, class:^(Signal|whatsapp|telegram|discord)$\nwindowrulev2 = workspace 4, class:^(Spotify|vlc|mpv)$\nwindowrulev2 = workspace 5, class:^(obsidian|thunderbird)$\n```\n\nThis ensures windows open in the correct workspace automatically."},{"id":"439053f7-407d-4b1c-ad2e-f284cd860857","title":"Create comprehensive documentation","description":"Create `~/.config/hypr/WORKSPACE_GUIDE.md` documenting:\n\n- Overview of the 10-workspace system\n- Keybindings reference (all workspace-related shortcuts)\n- Workspace naming conventions and default assignments\n- How to use the AI auto-organization feature\n- How to customize workspace rules in `workspace-rules.json`\n- How the learning system works in `workspace-learning.json`\n- Troubleshooting tips\n- Examples of common workflows\n\nInclude clear markdown formatting with sections, code blocks, and tables."},{"id":"504c5386-4e1a-4983-83a8-b8da44d48dd6","title":"Create workspace overview script","description":"Create `~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-overview` that provides a visual overview of all workspaces:\n\nThe script should:\n- Query all workspaces and their windows using `hyprctl workspaces -j` and `hyprctl clients -j`\n- Generate a formatted display showing each workspace with:\n  - Workspace number and name/label\n  - List of windows with titles\n  - Window counts\n  - Active workspace indicator\n- Display using rofi/wofi or generate HTML for a browser-based overview\n- Allow clicking/selecting to switch to a workspace\n\nMake the script executable: `chmod +x ~/.local/bin/hypr-workspace-overview`"},{"id":"52bbd10e-0198-4516-bbd8-25152d91e2f5","title":"Install hyprsome for enhanced workspace management","description":"Install hyprsome from the AUR to enable GNOME-like workspace behavior with automatic workspace creation/destruction:\n\n```bash\nyay -S hyprsome-git\n```\n\nThen add hyprsome to your Hyprland startup in `~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf` or the appropriate exec-once section."},{"id":"8d7efa80-f882-4d16-a59c-a1a43f63dc16","title":"Reload Hyprland configuration to apply all changes","description":"Execute the following command to reload the Hyprland configuration:\n\n```bash\nhyprctl reload\n```\n\nAlternatively, restart Hyprland completely if needed. This applies all the new bindings, window rules, and configuration changes."}],"pending_items":[]}],"conversation_usage_metadata":{"was_summarized":false,"context_window_usage":0.58844,"credits_spent":1235.4668,"credits_spent_for_last_block":26.369,"token_usage":[{"model_id":"claude 4.5 sonnet (thinking)","total_tokens":3042128,"byok_tokens":0},{"model_id":"claude 4.1 opus","total_tokens":3863288,"byok_tokens":0}],"tool_usage_metadata":{"run_command_stats":{"count":59,"commands_executed":58},"read_files_stats":{"count":10},"search_codebase_stats":{"count":0},"grep_stats":{"count":2},"file_glob_stats":{"count":4},"apply_file_diff_stats":{"count":15,"lines_added":37,"lines_removed":15,"files_changed":4},"write_to_long_running_shell_command_stats":{"count":0},"read_mcp_resource_stats":{"count":0},"call_mcp_tool_stats":{"count":0},"suggest_plan_stats":{"count":1},"suggest_create_plan_stats":{"count":1},"read_shell_command_output_stats":{"count":0}}}}|2025-11-11 03:18:35
82b81bc9-93a5-4d34-b8f3-32ed8ee3f545|{"server_conversation_token":"d4dddfe7-1308-42be-9808-40e96a6c42c7","todo_lists":[{"completed_items":[{"id":"14b59fd0-b5cb-48e1-bf02-f0827ca17aa0","title":"Create the smart screensaver wrapper script","description":"Create a new executable script at `/home/rob/.local/share/omarchy/bin/omarchy-smart-screensaver` that performs the following checks before launching the screensaver:\n\n1. **CPU Usage Check**: Read `/proc/stat` to calculate system CPU usage over a 1-second interval. Block screensaver if CPU usage is Ōēź10%.\n\n2. **Audio Playback Check**: Use `playerctl status` to detect if any media is currently playing. Block screensaver if status is \"Playing\".\n\n3. **Fullscreen Window Check**: Use `hyprctl clients -j` to get JSON data of all windows and check if any window has `\"fullscreen\": true`. Block screensaver if any fullscreen window exists.\n\n4. **Launch Screensaver**: If all checks pass (CPU < 10%, no audio playing, no fullscreen windows), execute `omarchy-launch-screensaver`.\n\nThe script should include proper error handling and exit gracefully if any command fails."},{"id":"1cdd3a3e-4fd7-4926-978e-c2c6d36e2c8a","title":"Make the smart screensaver script executable","description":"Set executable permissions on the newly created script:\n\n```bash\nchmod +x /home/rob/.local/share/omarchy/bin/omarchy-smart-screensaver\n```"},{"id":"9a817a48-b24a-4cc6-92d5-2aaece83bfb3","title":"Update hypridle.conf to use the smart wrapper and increase timeouts","description":"Modify `/home/rob/.config/hypr/hypridle.conf` with the following changes:\n\n1. **Line 9**: Change timeout from `150` to `600` (10 minutes for screensaver)\n2. **Line 10**: Change command from `pidof hyprlock || omarchy-launch-screensaver` to `pidof hyprlock || omarchy-smart-screensaver`\n3. **Line 14**: Change timeout from `300` to `1200` (20 minutes for lock screen)\n4. **Line 19**: Change timeout from `330` to `1320` (22 minutes for DPMS off)\n\nThis maintains proportional timing: screensaver at 10 min, lock screen at 20 min (2x), and DPMS off at 22 min (2.2x)."},{"id":"a679f9d6-5050-4390-8cc1-277b4e20c7bf","title":"Verify the implementation","description":"Test the new configuration to ensure:\n\n1. The smart wrapper script is executable and can be found in PATH\n2. The script correctly detects CPU usage, audio playback, and fullscreen windows\n3. The screensaver launches when conditions are met\n4. The existing screensaver toggle file check in `omarchy-launch-screensaver` still functions properly\n5. All timeout values are correctly updated in the hypridle configuration\n\nYou can test individual components by running the smart wrapper script manually and checking its behavior under different conditions."}],"pending_items":[]}],"conversation_usage_metadata":{"was_summarized":false,"context_window_usage":0.143985,"credits_spent":132.68903,"credits_spent_for_last_block":127.11228,"token_usage":[{"model_id":"claude 4.1 opus","total_tokens":199722,"byok_tokens":0},{"model_id":"claude 4.5 sonnet (thinking)","total_tokens":119263,"byok_tokens":0}],"tool_usage_metadata":{"run_command_stats":{"count":15,"commands_executed":15},"read_files_stats":{"count":3},"search_codebase_stats":{"count":0},"grep_stats":{"count":0},"file_glob_stats":{"count":1},"apply_file_diff_stats":{"count":3,"lines_added":17,"lines_removed":7,"files_changed":2},"write_to_long_running_shell_command_stats":{"count":0},"read_mcp_resource_stats":{"count":0},"call_mcp_tool_stats":{"count":0},"suggest_plan_stats":{"count":1},"suggest_create_plan_stats":{"count":1},"read_shell_command_output_stats":{"count":0}}}}|2025-11-11 03:02:12
2eaa2013-3902-4a45-811d-1a3fc0c7d4be|{"server_conversation_token":"ba3c5667-5d92-486c-94bc-1e866ec4dd18","todo_lists":[{"completed_items":[{"id":"db34497d-b625-4159-b136-403d2597dfd1","title":"Configure keyboard backlight with F5/F6 keys and OSD feedback","description":"Add keybindings to `~/.config/hypr/bindings.conf` for keyboard backlight control:\n\n```conf\n# Keyboard backlight controls\nbind = , XF86KbdBrightnessDown, exec, brightnessctl --device='smc::kbd_backlight' set 5%- && swayosd-client --brightness-keyboard $(brightnessctl --device='smc::kbd_backlight' get)\nbind = , XF86KbdBrightnessUp, exec, brightnessctl --device='smc::kbd_backlight' set 5%+ && swayosd-client --brightness-keyboard $(brightnessctl --device='smc::kbd_backlight' get)\n```\n\nVerify the device name is correct by running `brightnessctl -l` and adjust if needed. Test F5/F6 keys after reloading Hyprland config with `hyprctl reload`."},{"id":"d40b9d5b-4803-49d7-a6cb-73db9529f1ea","title":"Set up systemd service to restore keyboard backlight brightness on boot","description":"Create systemd service at `/etc/systemd/system/kbd-backlight-restore.service`:\n\n```ini\n[Unit]\nDescription=Restore keyboard backlight brightness\nAfter=multi-user.target\n\n[Service]\nType=oneshot\nExecStart=/usr/bin/brightnessctl --device='smc::kbd_backlight' set 128\n\n[Install]\nWantedBy=multi-user.target\n```\n\nEnable the service:\n```bash\nsudo systemctl enable kbd-backlight-restore.service\n```\n\nThis sets keyboard backlight to 50% (128/255) on boot. Adjust the value as preferred."},{"id":"052addb1-07a1-4ec5-9d2e-7d0f7b55f366","title":"Install cpupower and switch CPU governor to performance mode","description":"Install cpupower package:\n```bash\nsudo pacman -S cpupower\n```\n\nSet performance governor immediately:\n```bash\nsudo cpupower frequency-set -g performance\n```\n\nVerify the change:\n```bash\ncat /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu*/cpufreq/scaling_governor\n```\n\nAll cores should now show \"performance\" instead of \"schedutil\"."},{"id":"604b4ec4-7d3f-497a-9494-18905045252b","title":"Create systemd service for persistent performance governor on boot","description":"Create `/etc/systemd/system/cpupower-performance.service`:\n\n```ini\n[Unit]\nDescription=Set CPU governor to performance\nAfter=multi-user.target\n\n[Service]\nType=oneshot\nExecStart=/usr/bin/cpupower frequency-set -g performance\n\n[Install]\nWantedBy=multi-user.target\n```\n\nEnable the service:\n```bash\nsudo systemctl enable cpupower-performance.service\n```\n\nThis ensures performance governor is set on every boot."},{"id":"6dfacd9c-f5bc-4417-a6dd-407d43706724","title":"Configure or disable power-profiles-daemon for performance priority","description":"Check if power-profiles-daemon is running:\n```bash\nsystemctl status power-profiles-daemon\n```\n\nIf active, set it to performance profile:\n```bash\npowerprofilesctl set performance\n```\n\nOr disable it entirely to rely on cpupower:\n```bash\nsudo systemctl disable --now power-profiles-daemon\n```\n\nDisabling is recommended since we're using cpupower for maximum control."},{"id":"2cb1ff49-5203-45cd-a60a-22e1da1b1f7c","title":"Optimize swap configuration with swappiness tuning","description":"Check current swappiness:\n```bash\ncat /proc/sys/vm/swappiness\n```\n\nFor performance-focused setup, lower swappiness to 10:\n```bash\nsudo sysctl vm.swappiness=10\n```\n\nMake it persistent by adding to `/etc/sysctl.d/99-swappiness.conf`:\n```\nvm.swappiness=10\n```\n\nThis reduces swap usage, keeping more data in RAM for better performance."},{"id":"88eeae12-41c0-40ec-bc08-73d3b0ce7d84","title":"Create system monitoring dashboard script","description":"Create a comprehensive system status script at `~/bin/sysstatus`:\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\necho \"=== System Status ===\"\necho \"\"\necho \"CPU Governor:\"\ncat /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu0/cpufreq/scaling_governor\necho \"\"\necho \"CPU Frequency:\"\ncpupower frequency-info | grep \"current CPU frequency\"\necho \"\"\necho \"Memory Usage:\"\nfree -h\necho \"\"\necho \"Swap Usage:\"\nswapon --show\necho \"\"\necho \"Keyboard Backlight:\"\nbrightnessctl --device='smc::kbd_backlight' info\necho \"\"\necho \"Screen Backlight:\"\nbrightnessctl --device='intel_backlight' info\necho \"\"\necho \"Top Memory Processes:\"\nps aux --sort=-%mem | head -6\n```\n\nMake executable:\n```bash\nchmod +x ~/bin/sysstatus\n```\n\nRun anytime to check system optimization status:\n```bash\n~/bin/sysstatus\n```"},{"id":"e2c074f6-01e1-4294-bd01-703666827d1f","title":"Install and configure zram for compressed swap","description":"Install zram-generator:\n```bash\nsudo pacman -S zram-generator\n```\n\nCreate configuration at `/etc/systemd/zram-generator.conf`:\n```ini\n[zram0]\nzram-size = ram / 2\ncompression-algorithm = zstd\nswap-priority = 100\n```\n\nEnable and start:\n```bash\nsudo systemctl daemon-reload\nsudo systemctl start /dev/zram0\n```\n\nVerify with `zramctl` and `swapon --show`. This provides faster compressed swap than disk-based swap."},{"id":"1f895de2-304e-40a3-bbb7-1ff36ae0b979","title":"Install performance monitoring and system utilities","description":"Install comprehensive monitoring and system tools:\n\n```bash\n# Performance monitoring\nsudo pacman -S htop iotop powertop\n\n# System utilities\nsudo pacman -S preload earlyoom irqbalance\n\n# Enable useful services\nsudo systemctl enable --now preload\nsudo systemctl enable --now earlyoom\nsudo systemctl enable --now irqbalance\n```\n\n- **preload**: Predictively loads frequently-used apps into memory\n- **earlyoom**: Prevents system freezes from OOM situations\n- **irqbalance**: Distributes hardware interrupts across CPUs"},{"id":"b18e5a89-ee66-48d4-a214-ad7388038941","title":"Install modern terminal enhancements and CLI replacements","description":"Install enhanced terminal tools:\n\n```bash\n# Shell and prompt\nsudo pacman -S fish starship\n\n# Modern CLI tools\nsudo pacman -S fzf ripgrep bat fd zoxide\n\n# Wayland-specific tools\nsudo pacman -S wl-clipboard wev\n\n# Development tools\nsudo pacman -S github-cli\n```\n\nConfigure fish shell (optional):\n```bash\nchsh -s /usr/bin/fish\n```\n\nOr add starship to your current shell by adding to `~/.bashrc`:\n```bash\neval \"$(starship init bash)\"\n```"},{"id":"437c6dc0-612b-4a50-a62e-52f757c1ed65","title":"Set up Neovim with LazyVim distribution","description":"Install Neovim and dependencies:\n```bash\nsudo pacman -S neovim\n```\n\nBackup existing config and install LazyVim:\n```bash\nmv ~/.config/nvim ~/.config/nvim.bak\ngit clone https://github.com/LazyVim/starter ~/.config/nvim\nrm -rf ~/.config/nvim/.git\n```\n\nLaunch nvim to automatically install plugins:\n```bash\nnvim\n```\n\nInstall additional development tools:\n```bash\nsudo pacman -S lazygit\n```\n\nLazyVim integrates well with lazygit for Git management inside Neovim."},{"id":"0cc4aa76-93e7-4eae-8c21-bf10a6896183","title":"Install modern CLI productivity tools","description":"Install additional modern CLI replacements and productivity tools:\n\n```bash\n# Already have eza, add these\nsudo pacman -S duf dust procs\n\n# Backup solution\nyay -S timeshift\n\n# Additional useful tools\nsudo pacman -S ncdu  # Disk usage analyzer\nsudo pacman -S hyperfine  # Benchmarking tool\nsudo pacman -S tokei  # Code statistics\n```\n\nSet up aliases in `~/.bashrc` or `~/.config/fish/config.fish`:\n```bash\nalias df='duf'\nalias du='dust'\nalias ps='procs'\n```"},{"id":"f28ef6b5-121f-4413-8ea8-acc66b9f0d70","title":"Optimize pacman configuration for faster downloads","description":"Edit `/etc/pacman.conf` and enable:\n\n```ini\n# Misc options\nColor\nParallelDownloads = 5\n```\n\nClean package cache:\n```bash\nsudo pacman -Sc\n```\n\nInstall and configure paccache for automatic cleanup:\n```bash\nsudo pacman -S pacman-contrib\nsudo systemctl enable --now paccache.timer\n```\n\nThis automatically cleans old package versions weekly, keeping only the 3 most recent."},{"id":"b41530f4-b3cd-4b6e-9309-aa276e332e27","title":"Install and configure reflector for fastest Arch mirrors","description":"Install reflector:\n```bash\nsudo pacman -S reflector\n```\n\nGenerate fastest mirror list:\n```bash\nsudo reflector --country US --age 12 --protocol https --sort rate --save /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist\n```\n\nSet up automatic mirror updates with systemd timer:\n```bash\nsudo systemctl enable --now reflector.timer\n```\n\nConfigure reflector at `/etc/xdg/reflector/reflector.conf`:\n```\n--save /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist\n--country US\n--protocol https\n--latest 10\n--sort rate\n```\n\nAdjust `--country` based on your location for best results."},{"id":"b759ab48-ca75-4f63-9cf8-937054da9b87","title":"Install Python AI/ML tools using pipx","description":"Install pipx and Python AI tools:\n\n```bash\nsudo pacman -S python-pipx\npipx ensurepath\n\n# Install Jupyter and IPython\npipx install jupyter\npipx install ipython\n\n# Optional: Install additional AI/ML tools\npipx install notebook\n```\n\nVerify installations:\n```bash\njupyter --version\nipython --version\n```\n\nThese tools are now isolated in their own environments but globally accessible."},{"id":"ce32f9d0-c69c-4cd9-a213-47918ab6a8d8","title":"Install additional Hyprland ecosystem and GUI utilities","description":"Install Wayland/Hyprland GUI tools:\n\n```bash\n# Theme management\nsudo pacman -S nwg-look qt5ct qt6ct\n\n# Additional Hyprland tools\nsudo pacman -S wlogout\n\n# Install from AUR if needed\nyay -S hyprpicker\n```\n\nConfigure Qt theme tools by setting environment variables in `~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf`:\n```conf\nenv = QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME,qt5ct\n```\n\nRun `nwg-look` to configure GTK themes and `qt5ct` for Qt themes."},{"id":"86de299d-b872-40ca-9c3e-4e0c3578ed67","title":"Optimize Intel HD Graphics 6000 drivers","description":"Ensure latest Intel graphics drivers are installed:\n\n```bash\nsudo pacman -S mesa lib32-mesa vulkan-intel lib32-vulkan-intel intel-media-driver\n```\n\nAdd Intel graphics optimizations to `/etc/environment`:\n```\nMESA_LOADER_DRIVER_OVERRIDE=iris\nLIBVA_DRIVER_NAME=iHD\n```\n\nFor Hyprland, verify these environment variables in `~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf`:\n```conf\nenv = WLR_DRM_NO_ATOMIC,1\nenv = WLR_RENDERER_ALLOW_SOFTWARE,1\n```\n\nThese may help with older Intel graphics compatibility on Wayland."},{"id":"a63f5d0e-af2d-49e9-9bba-4752cf9a763e","title":"Install Ollama and AI CLI tools for local LLM capabilities","description":"Install Ollama:\n```bash\ncurl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\n```\n\nStart Ollama service:\n```bash\nsudo systemctl enable --now ollama\n```\n\nPull a model to test:\n```bash\nollama pull llama3.2\n```\n\nInstall AI CLI tools:\n```bash\n# Install via AUR\nyay -S aichat shell-gpt\n\n# Configure aichat for Ollama\nmkdir -p ~/.config/aichat\necho 'model: ollama:llama3.2' > ~/.config/aichat/config.yaml\n```\n\nTest with:\n```bash\naichat \"Hello, test message\"\n```"},{"id":"d5cd3430-830d-4cbb-befc-8b8f2fe8ef21","title":"Verify and optimize Apple kernel modules","description":"Check loaded Apple modules:\n```bash\nlsmod | grep -E \"apple|smc|hid\"\n```\n\nEnsure these modules are loaded:\n- applesmc (SMC sensor support)\n- hid_apple (keyboard/trackpad)\n- snd_hda_codec_cirrus (audio)\n\nCreate `/etc/modprobe.d/hid_apple.conf` for keyboard optimizations:\n```\noptions hid_apple fnmode=2\noptions hid_apple swap_opt_cmd=1\n```\n\n- `fnmode=2`: Function keys work as F1-F12 by default (press Fn for media keys)\n- `swap_opt_cmd=1`: Swaps Alt and Command keys to match PC keyboard layout\n\nRegenerate initramfs:\n```bash\nsudo mkinitcpio -P\n```\n\nReboot to apply kernel module changes."},{"id":"76bab89e-3def-4dc7-9964-a650bdcd9805","title":"Configure enhanced touchpad gestures in Hyprland","description":"Add touchpad gesture configuration to `~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf`:\n\n```conf\ngestures {\n    workspace_swipe = true\n    workspace_swipe_fingers = 3\n    workspace_swipe_distance = 300\n    workspace_swipe_invert = true\n    workspace_swipe_min_speed_to_force = 30\n    workspace_swipe_cancel_ratio = 0.5\n    workspace_swipe_create_new = true\n}\n\ninput {\n    touchpad {\n        natural_scroll = true\n        tap-to-click = true\n        drag_lock = true\n        disable_while_typing = true\n    }\n}\n```\n\nReload Hyprland config:\n```bash\nhyprctl reload\n```\n\nTest three-finger swipe for workspace switching."},{"id":"83f30fe1-cd85-4992-960a-68f8ddd5f4a0","title":"Set up comprehensive Wayland environment variables","description":"Add these environment variables to `~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf` for better application compatibility:\n\n```conf\nenv = XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP,Hyprland\nenv = XDG_SESSION_TYPE,wayland\nenv = XDG_SESSION_DESKTOP,Hyprland\n\nenv = QT_QPA_PLATFORM,wayland;xcb\nenv = QT_WAYLAND_DISABLE_WINDOWDECORATION,1\nenv = QT_AUTO_SCREEN_SCALE_FACTOR,1\n\nenv = GDK_BACKEND,wayland,x11\nenv = SDL_VIDEODRIVER,wayland\nenv = CLUTTER_BACKEND,wayland\n\nenv = MOZ_ENABLE_WAYLAND,1\nenv = ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT,wayland\n```\n\nThese ensure applications prefer Wayland over XWayland when possible, improving performance and reducing latency."},{"id":"175ddfdb-efc2-4a08-9a95-ce24d081b3de","title":"Verify mise configuration for optimal development environment","description":"Since mise is already installed, verify and optimize configuration:\n\n```bash\n# Check current mise status\nmise doctor\n\n# List installed tools\nmise list\n\n# Update mise itself\nmise self-update\n\n# Update all installed tools\nmise upgrade\n```\n\nAdd auto-activation to your shell config (`~/.bashrc`):\n```bash\neval \"$(mise activate bash)\"\n```\n\nOr for fish shell (`~/.config/fish/config.fish`):\n```fish\nmise activate fish | source\n```\n\nConfigure mise at `~/.config/mise/config.toml` for commonly used tools:\n```toml\n[tools]\nnode = \"lts\"\npython = \"3.12\"\n```\n\nThis ensures consistent development environments across projects."},{"id":"fb31a91b-f6df-4d54-883a-aa141c425da7","title":"Review and disable unnecessary systemd services","description":"List all enabled services:\n```bash\nsystemctl list-unit-files --state=enabled\n```\n\nIdentify and disable unnecessary services. Common candidates:\n```bash\n# Example: Disable Bluetooth if not used\nsudo systemctl disable bluetooth.service\n\n# Disable ModemManager if no cellular modem\nsudo systemctl disable ModemManager.service\n```\n\nCheck boot time to identify slow services:\n```bash\nsystemd-analyze blame\nsystemd-analyze critical-chain\n```\n\nOnly disable services you're certain aren't needed. Research each before disabling."},{"id":"efeed03d-18dd-41cc-ad75-bcb626de6e64","title":"Set up GUI brightness control via waybar module","description":"Add brightness module to waybar config at `~/.config/waybar/config`:\n\n```json\n\"backlight\": {\n    \"device\": \"intel_backlight\",\n    \"format\": \"{icon} {percent}%\",\n    \"format-icons\": [\"\", \"\", \"\", \"\", \"\", \"\", \"\", \"\", \"\"],\n    \"on-scroll-up\": \"brightnessctl set 5%+\",\n    \"on-scroll-down\": \"brightnessctl set 5%-\",\n    \"on-click\": \"brightnessctl set 100%\",\n    \"on-click-right\": \"brightnessctl set 10%\"\n}\n```\n\nAdd keyboard backlight module:\n```json\n\"custom/kbd-backlight\": {\n    \"format\": \"Ōī© {}%\",\n    \"exec\": \"brightnessctl --device='smc::kbd_backlight' get | awk '{print int($1/2.55)}'\",\n    \"interval\": 1,\n    \"on-scroll-up\": \"brightnessctl --device='smc::kbd_backlight' set 5%+\",\n    \"on-scroll-down\": \"brightnessctl --device='smc::kbd_backlight' set 5%-\"\n}\n```\n\nRestart waybar to apply changes."},{"id":"c346fa95-ae0e-4d1a-ad17-366057f86458","title":"Install MacBook-specific hardware optimization tools","description":"Install MacBook fan control and Apple-specific utilities:\n\n```bash\n# Fan control for MacBook\nyay -S mbpfan-git\n\n# Enable and start fan control\nsudo systemctl enable --now mbpfan\n\n# Apple-specific features (if needed)\nyay -S pommed-light\n```\n\nConfigure mbpfan at `/etc/mbpfan.conf` (adjust temperatures as needed):\n```ini\n[general]\nmin_fan_speed = 2000\nmax_fan_speed = 6200\nlow_temp = 55\nhigh_temp = 65\nmax_temp = 80\n```\n\nRestart mbpfan after configuration changes:\n```bash\nsudo systemctl restart mbpfan\n```"},{"id":"484580aa-c1d6-4037-9cf4-be117cc780bb","title":"Install alternative AI GUI applications","description":"Install GUI alternatives for AI/LLM interaction:\n\n```bash\n# Jan.ai (Electron-based, user-friendly)\nyay -S jan-bin\n\n# Or LM Studio alternative\nyay -S lm-studio-bin\n```\n\nBoth provide graphical interfaces for:\n- Managing local LLM models\n- Chat interfaces\n- Model parameter tuning\n- Integration with Ollama\n\nLaunch with:\n```bash\njan\n# or\nlm-studio\n```\n\nThese complement Ollama for users who prefer GUI over CLI for AI interactions."},{"id":"3837872b-64e4-4192-adf5-5b9de15b0c94","title":"Optimize memory usage and identify memory-hungry processes","description":"Analyze current memory usage:\n```bash\nps aux --sort=-%mem | head -20\nfree -h\n```\n\nBased on analysis showing Beeper (20%), Warp (6.8%), and Chromium (4.5%) as top consumers:\n\n1. **Consider alternatives**:\n   - Replace Warp with lighter terminal (kitty, foot, or alacritty)\n   - Use Firefox instead of Chromium (typically lighter)\n\n2. **Install process monitoring**:\n```bash\nsudo pacman -S memavaild\nsudo systemctl enable --now memavaild\n```\n\n3. **Add memory pressure monitoring** to waybar:\n```json\n\"memory\": {\n    \"format\": \"¾░Źø {}%\",\n    \"format-alt\": \"¾░Źø {used}GiB/{total}GiB\",\n    \"interval\": 5,\n    \"states\": {\n        \"warning\": 70,\n        \"critical\": 90\n    }\n}\n```\n\nMonitor memory usage and close/restart heavy applications when needed."}],"pending_items":[{"id":"da1c6dc2-ba53-4235-a6cf-e3594b746893","title":"Final verification and system reboot","description":"Verify all configurations are in place:\n\n1. **Check systemd services**:\n```bash\nsystemctl status kbd-backlight-restore\nsystemctl status cpupower-performance\nsystemctl status mbpfan\nsystemctl status preload\nsystemctl status earlyoom\n```\n\n2. **Verify kernel parameters**:\n```bash\ncat /proc/sys/vm/swappiness\n```\n\n3. **Test keyboard backlight controls**: Press F5 and F6 to verify OSD feedback\n\n4. **Check CPU governor**:\n```bash\ncat /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu*/cpufreq/scaling_governor\n```\n\n5. **Reboot to ensure all changes persist**:\n```bash\nsystemctl reboot\n```\n\nAfter reboot, run the `~/bin/sysstatus` script to verify all optimizations are active."}]}],"conversation_usage_metadata":{"was_summarized":true,"context_window_usage":0.233185,"credits_spent":354.77893,"credits_spent_for_last_block":1.22692,"token_usage":[{"model_id":"claude 4.5 sonnet (thinking)","total_tokens":12297308,"byok_tokens":0}],"tool_usage_metadata":{"run_command_stats":{"count":115,"commands_executed":114},"read_files_stats":{"count":13},"search_codebase_stats":{"count":0},"grep_stats":{"count":0},"file_glob_stats":{"count":0},"apply_file_diff_stats":{"count":14,"lines_added":47,"lines_removed":30,"files_changed":3},"write_to_long_running_shell_command_stats":{"count":0},"read_mcp_resource_stats":{"count":0},"call_mcp_tool_stats":{"count":0},"suggest_plan_stats":{"count":1},"suggest_create_plan_stats":{"count":1},"read_shell_command_output_stats":{"count":0}}}}|2025-11-11 02:34:15
13486f10-a810-4d21-b459-8255e3328b21|{"server_conversation_token":"982c4556-3ede-4df1-b145-314fd18faac9","todo_lists":[{"completed_items":[{"id":"dd3292fe-4451-4d3e-bb3c-55a1c06aa9c7","title":"Check current monitor configuration with hyprctl","description":"Run `hyprctl monitors` to identify the current monitor name, resolution, and scale settings. This will confirm we're targeting the correct monitor (likely eDP-1 based on the context)."},{"id":"8d5484e1-3939-4ae9-8815-9301bc84f502","title":"Update monitors.conf to set initial scale to 1.5","description":"Modify `/home/rob/.config/hypr/monitors.conf` to set the monitor scale to 1.5 for monitor eDP-1:\n- Change the monitor line to include scale parameter: `monitor=eDP-1,preferred,auto,1.5`\n- Also update or add the GDK_SCALE environment variable to 1.5: `env = GDK_SCALE,1.5`\n- Preserve any existing xwayland force_zero_scaling settings"},{"id":"50a6afc1-bc53-42d7-ac16-064231f96d17","title":"Create the omarchy-scale-switcher script","description":"Create `/home/rob/.local/share/omarchy/bin/omarchy-scale-switcher` with the following functionality:\n- Define scale options: 1.0, 1.25, 1.5, 1.75, 2.0\n- Use walker (omarchy-launch-walker) to present a menu of these options\n- When user selects a scale:\n  - Apply live via `hyprctl keyword monitor eDP-1,preferred,auto,[SCALE]`\n  - Update monitors.conf file by replacing the scale value in the monitor line\n  - Update GDK_SCALE environment variable in monitors.conf\n  - Send a notification via `notify-send` confirming the scale change\n- Make the script executable with `chmod +x`"},{"id":"7af6a5c1-47fb-4068-a3d3-32bdb8fb52f1","title":"Add keybinding for scale-switcher","description":"Add a keybinding in `/home/rob/.config/hypr/bindings.conf` to launch the scale-switcher:\n- Add line: `bind = SUPER SHIFT, S, exec, omarchy-scale-switcher`\n- Follow the existing Omarchy keybinding patterns in the file"},{"id":"186c0373-2e93-4431-a6da-ba3e8c4ad26e","title":"Reload Hyprland configuration","description":"Apply the initial configuration changes by reloading Hyprland:\n- Run `hyprctl reload` to apply the new monitor scale and keybinding\n- Verify the scale has been applied with `hyprctl monitors`\n- Test the keybinding (SUPER SHIFT + S) to ensure the scale-switcher launches properly"}],"pending_items":[]}],"conversation_usage_metadata":{"was_summarized":false,"context_window_usage":0.164795,"credits_spent":30.81195,"credits_spent_for_last_block":22.15487,"token_usage":[{"model_id":"claude 4.5 sonnet (thinking)","total_tokens":619412,"byok_tokens":0}],"tool_usage_metadata":{"run_command_stats":{"count":17,"commands_executed":17},"read_files_stats":{"count":5},"search_codebase_stats":{"count":0},"grep_stats":{"count":1},"file_glob_stats":{"count":1},"apply_file_diff_stats":{"count":3,"lines_added":5,"lines_removed":2,"files_changed":2},"write_to_long_running_shell_command_stats":{"count":0},"read_mcp_resource_stats":{"count":0},"call_mcp_tool_stats":{"count":0},"suggest_plan_stats":{"count":1},"suggest_create_plan_stats":{"count":1},"read_shell_command_output_stats":{"count":0}}}}|2025-11-10 22:42:47
e88be939-86a2-4d14-9096-377ff95ce257|{"server_conversation_token":"70dc4be5-3cff-4bea-a957-607d4402ab78","todo_lists":[{"completed_items":[{"id":"faa38eae-84cf-4847-830b-93ecce654d82","title":"Check current sudo configuration for user 'rob'","description":"Verify the current sudoers configuration by examining `/etc/sudoers.d/00_rob` to understand the existing rule that needs to be modified.\n\nCommand: `sudo cat /etc/sudoers.d/00_rob`"},{"id":"a0599939-a817-41e6-9cd3-35dcd80eb446","title":"Create backup of sudoers configuration","description":"Before making changes, create a backup of the current sudoers configuration file to enable rollback if needed.\n\nCommand: `sudo cp /etc/sudoers.d/00_rob /etc/sudoers.d/00_rob.backup`"},{"id":"95740ac3-4ba2-43eb-a81e-71c6ea0c334a","title":"Modify sudoers file to enable passwordless sudo","description":"Edit the sudoers configuration file using `visudo` (the safe way) to change the rule for user 'rob' from `rob ALL=(ALL) ALL` to `rob ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL`.\n\nCommand: `sudo EDITOR=tee visudo -f /etc/sudoers.d/00_rob`\n\nThe new content should be:\n```\nrob ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL\n```\n\nThis will allow user 'rob' to execute all sudo commands without password prompts."},{"id":"14649088-0aed-42b2-ac98-990d6f9bfa28","title":"Verify the sudoers syntax","description":"Check that the sudoers file has valid syntax using visudo's check mode.\n\nCommand: `sudo visudo -c -f /etc/sudoers.d/00_rob`\n\nThis ensures no syntax errors were introduced that could lock you out of sudo access."},{"id":"14c7d64c-996c-40ed-b65f-97725289b52b","title":"Test passwordless sudo functionality","description":"Test that passwordless sudo is working correctly by running a simple sudo command.\n\nCommand: `sudo whoami`\n\nThis should execute without prompting for a password and return 'root'."}],"pending_items":[]}],"conversation_usage_metadata":{"was_summarized":false,"context_window_usage":0.098365,"credits_spent":11.795723,"credits_spent_for_last_block":8.02242,"token_usage":[{"model_id":"claude 4.5 sonnet (thinking)","total_tokens":162416,"byok_tokens":0}],"tool_usage_metadata":{"run_command_stats":{"count":10,"commands_executed":10},"read_files_stats":{"count":0},"search_codebase_stats":{"count":0},"grep_stats":{"count":0},"file_glob_stats":{"count":0},"apply_file_diff_stats":{"count":0,"lines_added":0,"lines_removed":0,"files_changed":0},"write_to_long_running_shell_command_stats":{"count":0},"read_mcp_resource_stats":{"count":0},"call_mcp_tool_stats":{"count":0},"suggest_plan_stats":{"count":1},"suggest_create_plan_stats":{"count":1},"read_shell_command_output_stats":{"count":0}}}}|2025-11-10 22:30:03
76105fe0-e7f8-46c9-bdf3-32d3826dbbaf|{"server_conversation_token":"dc66a2cc-2ca9-40db-86e3-7bf85b96610c","todo_lists":[{"completed_items":[{"id":"afc79ef1-39f7-4cff-91e4-6ae483bb2bd5","title":"Set system-wide default keyboard layout to pt-br using localectl","description":"Run `localectl set-keymap br` to set the console keymap and `localectl set-x11-keymap br` to configure the X11/Wayland keymap. This ensures pt-br is the default layout system-wide and persists across reboots.\n\nVerify the configuration with `localectl status` to confirm both VC Keymap and X11 Layout are set to \"br\"."},{"id":"6f397647-ac26-474d-8945-30c8dc3c524d","title":"Configure Hyprland input settings for multiple keyboard layouts","description":"Edit `/home/rob/.config/hypr/input.conf` to add or modify the keyboard configuration:\n\n```\ninput {\n    kb_layout = br,us\n    kb_options = grp:alt_shift_toggle\n    repeat_rate = 50\n    repeat_delay = 300\n    numlock_by_default = true\n    \n    # Preserve existing touchpad settings\n    touchpad {\n        natural_scroll = false\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis sets pt-br (br) as the primary layout and us as secondary, with Alt+Shift as the toggle key. Preserve any existing settings like repeat_rate, repeat_delay, and touchpad configuration."},{"id":"e9f10d89-33cf-42e0-ac59-c7cceb55a58f","title":"Add keyboard layout indicator to Waybar configuration","description":"Edit `/home/rob/.config/waybar/config.jsonc` to add the \"hyprland/language\" module. Add it to the \"modules-right\" or \"modules-center\" array:\n\n```json\n\"hyprland/language\": {\n    \"format\": \"Ōī© {}\",\n    \"format-br\": \"BR\",\n    \"format-us\": \"US\",\n    \"on-click\": \"hyprctl switchxkblayout at-translated-set-2-keyboard next\"\n}\n```\n\nNote: The device name \"at-translated-set-2-keyboard\" may need to be adjusted based on the output of `hyprctl devices -j | grep keyboard`. Use the actual keyboard device name shown in the system."},{"id":"13e546ee-e7fb-4421-8bf4-43ae58b32758","title":"Add styling for the keyboard layout indicator in Waybar","description":"Edit `/home/rob/.config/waybar/style.css` to add styling for the language module:\n\n```css\n#language {\n    background-color: #2e3440;\n    color: #d8dee9;\n    padding: 0 10px;\n    margin: 0 4px;\n    border-radius: 5px;\n}\n\n#language:hover {\n    background-color: #3b4252;\n    cursor: pointer;\n}\n```\n\nAdjust colors to match the existing Waybar theme if needed."},{"id":"dfdab582-fdde-49de-8d2e-801dbf192423","title":"Add optional Hyprland keybinding for manual layout switching","description":"Edit the Hyprland bindings configuration file (typically `/home/rob/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf` or a separate bindings file) to add:\n\n```\nbind = SUPER, SPACE, exec, hyprctl switchxkblayout at-translated-set-2-keyboard next\n```\n\nThis allows switching layouts with Super+Space in addition to Alt+Shift. Adjust the keybinding as preferred, and ensure the keyboard device name matches the actual device."},{"id":"8f7bdd69-2f0b-4167-b874-6ba0ad938987","title":"Reload Hyprland configuration and restart Waybar","description":"Apply the changes by reloading Hyprland configuration with `hyprctl reload` and restarting Waybar with `killall waybar && waybar &`.\n\nAlternatively, log out and log back in to ensure all changes take effect. Verify that:\n- The Waybar shows the current keyboard layout\n- Clicking the layout indicator switches between br and us\n- Alt+Shift toggles between layouts\n- The default layout is pt-br after reboot"}],"pending_items":[]}],"conversation_usage_metadata":{"was_summarized":false,"context_window_usage":0.204605,"credits_spent":35.40781,"credits_spent_for_last_block":45.65665,"token_usage":[{"model_id":"claude 4.5 sonnet (thinking)","total_tokens":1024416,"byok_tokens":0}],"tool_usage_metadata":{"run_command_stats":{"count":17,"commands_executed":17},"read_files_stats":{"count":2},"search_codebase_stats":{"count":0},"grep_stats":{"count":0},"file_glob_stats":{"c